<chapter xml:id="configuration" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0CR7/xsd/docbook.xsd">
  <title>Configuration</title>

  <qandaset>
    <qandaentry xml:id="configuration.props">
      <question>
        <para>
          I need some custom java properties for my application. Where should I put them?
        </para>
      </question>
      <answer>
        <para>
          You can add those in the <literal>&lt;properties/&gt;</literal> section of your servlet configuration file.
          For example at the end of your <filename>app.conf.xml</filename> you can have something like:
        </para>
        <programlisting language="xml"><![CDATA[<properties>
  <prop name="jdbc_conn_string">jdbc:mysql://foo/bar</prop>
</properties>]]></programlisting>
      </answer>
    </qandaentry>
  </qandaset>

</chapter>